Company Overview of Ariel Investment Trust - Ariel Appreciation Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Ariel Investment Trust - Ariel Appreciation Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Ariel Investments, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in the value stocks of mid cap companies with a market capitalization between $2 billion and $15 billion. It employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as capital appreciation over time, high barriers to entry, sustainable competitive advantages, predictable fundamentals that allow for double-digit earnings growth, skilled management teams and solid financials to create its portfolio. The fund be...
Ariel Investment Trust - Ariel Appreciation Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Ariel Investments, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in the value stocks of mid cap companies with a market capitalization between $2 billion and $15 billion. It employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as capital appreciation over time, high barriers to entry, sustainable competitive advantages, predictable fundamentals that allow for double-digit earnings growth, skilled management teams and solid financials to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell Midcap Value Index, the Russell Midcap Index, and the S&P 500 Index. It employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. The fund does not invest in corporations whose primary source of revenue is derived from the production or sale of tobacco products or the manufacture of handguns. Ariel Investment Trust - Ariel Appreciation Fund was formed on December 1, 1989 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


