Description

Ariel Investments is a money management firm founded in 1983 and headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. Since our founding by John W. Rogers, Jr., we have grown from two to 86 employees with $9 billion in assets under management. Taking a long-term view and applying independent thinking to our investment decisions, we now span the market cap spectrum from micro to large, and cover the world with our international and global offerings. In addition to managing separate accounts for corporate, public, union, and non-profit organizations, we also serve as the investment adviser for Ariel Investment Trust—comprising six no-load, publicly traded mutual funds, which are available to institutional and individual investors, financial intermediaries and defined contribution plans. Under Ariel’s time-tested patient investing philosophy, we have managed small cap value portfolios since the firm’s inception and our flagship Ariel Fund, representing our small/mid cap value strategy, dates back to 1986. Our mid cap value style, which includes Ariel Appreciation Fund, was introduced in 1989. We launched our all-cap focused value strategy, including Ariel Focus Fund, in 2005. In 2009, we added a deep value approach via a micro-cap value product, with an excellent track record that dates back to 2002. We expanded this lineup in 2011 with a small cap deep value mutual fund, Ariel Discovery Fund, as well as a separate account in October 2013.At the end of 2011, Ariel launched international and global separate accounts and mutual funds, also with a long-term approach. The team managing these portfolios is based in our New York office.









